# LAMMPS Input File
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# A Set of Tutorials for the LAMMPS Simulation Package (LiveCoMS, 2025)
# By Simon Gravelle, Cecilia M. S. Alvares, Jacob R. Gissinger, and Axel Kohlmeyer
# Please cite doi.org/10.33011/livecoms.6.1.3037
# Find more on GitHub: https://github.com/lammpstutorials

# 1. Initialization & Logging
log cracking_reax.log
units real          # CRITICAL: ReaxFF uses real units (fs, kcal/mol)
boundary p p p
atom_style full

read_data generate.data

# 2. ReaxFF Force Field & Charge Equilibration
pair_style reaxff NULL
pair_coeff * * ffield.reax.SiOH Si O
fix qeq all qeq/reaxff 1 0.0 10.0 1.0e-6 reaxff  # Using the updated keyword!

# 3. Output & Visualization (4x Multiplier applied)
dump ovito_dump all custom 1000 cracking_traj.lammpstrj id type element x y z
dump_modify ovito_dump element Si O

thermo 1000
thermo_style custom step temp etotal vol density

# 4. Deformation & Run Settings
timestep 0.25       # CRITICAL: ReaxFF requires 0.25 fs timestep
fix nvt1 all nvt temp 300 300 100.0   # Tdamp is 100.0 for real units

# CRITICAL: The deformation rate must be divided by 1000 because we moved from picoseconds to femtoseconds!
# Old rate: 0.005 / ps  --> New rate: 0.000005 / fs
fix mydef all deform 1 x erate 0.000005

# 4x Multiplier applied to match the exact same physical time (50 ps total)
run 200000

write_data cracking.data
